description:
An action dexterity game. Each player has a plastic fly-swat. The wasps are scattered in the room and it is a race to see who can 'Squasp' the most wasps. The wasps are made in such a way that they will stick to the fly-swat easily.
Sold with the line;
"Just squash the wasp by his sting - swat the lot 'n' you'll be king"

The gates have opened: Embark on a perilous journey into the nether realms of the &bdquo;Underworld&ldquo;. Command hordes of mindless undead minions. Summon the mighty and vicious Archdemon to bring terror and destruction upon your foe. Foil your opponent&rsquo;s evil plans with nifty counter-magic and even meddle with the very fabric of space and time to go forth victorious from the epic battles fought in the &ldquo;Underworld&rdquo;.

The first Expansion Set for Elemental Clash, &ldquo;Underworld&rdquo;, brings you 66 all new cards to customize and enhance your Basic Set decks. Apart from many exciting and powerful colored ones, &ldquo;Underworld&rdquo; introduces neutral Creatures and Spells. Furthermore, the new &ldquo;Double Element Stones&rdquo; can be utilized to make multi-element decks even more viable and efficient. So do not fear, young wizard apprentice, and delve into the dark depths of the &ldquo;Underworld&rdquo;

The aim of the game is to reduce the cards in your opponent&rsquo;s card-deck (or Spellbook) to zero by using the Spells and Creatures in your Spellbook. Players take turns that always follow the same structure. For each point of damage a Player receives through Creatures or Spells, he or she puts the top card of his or her deck on his or her Discard Pile (or Archive). Is a player unable to draw a card, he or she loses immediately.

This game simulates a football match.
 Each player builds his own team by buying pieces until you reach the number of points determined at the beginning of the game.
 Each piece has a different buying value. Pieces are marked on the values ​​of defense, attack, movement and power of the player that they represent.
 It possible deploy its own team in the field with the classic patterns of football: 3-5-2, 4-4-2, 4-3-3 (defenders-midfielders-forwards).
 A match lasts two periods of 16 rounds for a total of 32 rounds.
 There is also a deck of cards to use in contrast, to determine if any foul actions.
 Components of the game:
 1 board;
 68 pieces players divided  into two teams;
 72 card comparison;
 2 pieces ball;
 1 die;
 regulation

We get Freddy Krueger, Freddy Nightmare Worm, Jason Voorhees, Jason Carrying Freddy's Head, and the final uberpiece, Freddy And Jason Together (featuring both figures on a single base). It is worth noting that the scenarios that come with the rulebook do not recommend using this last piece&hellip;

The figures are 28mm, and of fine quality, although the factory paint jobs leave a bit to be desired. And for those of you wishing to rebase, they'll come off easily enough (and provide SIX figures rather than five; the Jason Vs. Freddy piece can be separated).

Altogether, a neat tabletop game awaits. Make a neat main event for this coming Halloween, and a nice diversion from the usual zombie geek bingo events&hellip;

This is actually a Licensed Starter/Expansion style pack for Horrorclix, and doesn't really work as a stand alone game.

The nations of Europe are falling one by one to a ruthless and powerful enemy&hellip;

Secretly, in their forest and mountain strongholds, armies of courageous volunteers are organizing themselves to fight for their nation, or die in its defense!

&ldquo;For Freedom!&rdquo; is a tabletop, card-based, strategy game played between two people. Each player takes command of one of two opposing nations from World War II. Use each card cleverly to attack your opponent and his resources, while defending your own!

Whom will YOU command?

Wehrmacht &ndash; command the Blitzkrieg of Nazi Germany to encircle and destroy your enemy with tanks and aircraft. Don&rsquo;t let your compassion keep you from victory&hellip;

Ukrainian Insurgent Army &ndash; command the partisan troops of the UIA in raids and sabotage operations to break the attack of your enemy. Don&rsquo;t let the conqueror destroy your homeland and take away your freedom!


        UNAUTHORIZED PRODUCTION



         The information that BGG has on this item indicates that San Guo Sha is an unauthorized reproduction of BANG! with just a few differences, published in China and distributed in several coutries of the world.




This is the fourth character expansion of San Guo Sha, or the Killers of the Three Kingdoms. This expansion introduces 10 new characters including 8 ordinary characters and 2 Demi-God characters randomly inserted into some packets.

The 10 characters are:

Shu Kingdom: Liu Chan, Jiang Wei;
Wei Kingdom: Zhang He, Deng Ai;
Wu Kingdom: Sun Ce, Zhang Zhao&Zhang Hong[1]; 
Qun: Zuo Ci, Cai Wenji.  
Two Demi-God: God Si Mayi, God Zhao Yun.

[1] Zhang Zhao&Zhang Hong are two characters on the same card, like Yan Liang&Wen Zhou in the Fire Expansion）

A simple roll and move game for the very young. Children will need a little luck to be the first to find the letters that matches the character name on their postcard. It is a nicely themed game about this popular children's TV favourite.

From the publisher;
Today is total mayhem at the sorting office! Letters are everywhere and no-one know what to do, so Pat has no choice but to stop his deliveries and help sort out the mess! Players each have a postcard belonging to a resident of Greendale, then race around the sorting office turning over the jumble of post to find the missing letters. The first to find all their missing letters from their postcard is the winner!
